<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-130-160  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 130 160.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Vision Graphics andamp; Image Processing  Feb 1989 v45 n2p167(29).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A nonlinear Laplace operator as edge detector in noisy images.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>van Vliet, Lucas J.; Young, Ian T.; Beckers, Guus L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The extraction of useful and relevant edges is a major problem indigital image processing and scene analysis.andP;  An edge-detectionscheme robust enough to perform well over a broad range ofsignal-to-noise ratios is presented.andP;  The scheme is based on thedetection of zero crossings in the output image of a nonlinearLaplace filter, with specific characterizations of the filter asits adaptive orientation to the gradient and its inherent maskspermitting the development of isotropic filters.andP;  Quantitativeevaluation shows the edge detector as at least equal to, and inmost cases better than, other edge detectors, particularly at verylow signal-to-noise ratios, when it is superior to all otherfilters.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Edge DetectionFiltersNoiseImage ProcessingScene Analysis.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   The edge detection model. (chart)The zero crossing detection scheme. (chart)Comparison of equivalent noise suppression - uniform and Gaussianfilters. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>